  "ai_usage": "Great for hero taglines and terminal/CLI aesthetics. Pure-CSS version requires: a monospace font, the text wrapped in an inline-block element, ch-based width animation, and --chars set to the exact character count. For dynamic/looping text, prefer a tiny JS loop that swaps textContent. Keep white-space:nowrap and overflow:hidden.",
  "path": "effects/text-effects/typewriter-text.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Typewriter Text</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"typewriter-text\",\n    \"title\": \"Typewriter Text\",\n    \"summary\": \"Text types itself out with a blinking caret using the steps() timing function.\",\n    \"description\": \"Animates max-width / width from 0 with steps() so characters appear one glyph at a time, plus a border-right caret that blinks.\",\n    \"theme\": \"text-effects\",\n    \"categories\": [\"typography\", \"animation\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"typewriter\", \"typing\", \"steps\", \"caret\", \"monospace\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\"],\n    \"era\": \"2010s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All modern browsers. The pure-CSS version needs a known character count and a monospace font.\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"Animating width triggers layout but on a single short line it is negligible.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Full text is present in the DOM immediately (just visually clipped), so screen readers get it. Animation is skipped under prefers-reduced-motion (text shown instantly).\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"--chars\", \"description\": \"Number of characters (set to your text length)\", \"default\": \"11\" },\n      { \"name\": \"--speed\", \"description\": \"Typing duration\", \"default\": \"3s\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Loop with multiple phrases via JS\", \"Solid block caret instead of bar\", \"Remove caret after typing with a forwards fill\"],\n    \"related\": [\"text-reveal-mask\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Great for hero taglines and terminal/CLI aesthetics. Pure-CSS version requires: a monospace font, the text wrapped in an inline-block element, ch-based width animation, and --chars set to the exact character count. For dynamic/looping text, prefer a tiny JS loop that swaps textContent. Keep white-space:nowrap and overflow:hidden.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root { --chars: 11; --speed: 3s; }\n    html, body { height: 100%; margin: 0; }\n    body { display: grid; place-items: center; background: #0b0d12; font-family: ui-monospace, \"Courier New\", monospace; }\n    .typewriter {\n      font-size: 2.2rem; color: #34d399; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden;\n      border-right: 0.12em solid #34d399;\n      width: 0;\n      animation: typing var(--speed) steps(var(--chars)) forwards, caret 0.8s step-end infinite;\n    }\n    @keyframes typing { to { width: calc(var(--chars) * 1ch); } }\n    @keyframes caret { 50% { border-color: transparent; } }\n    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {\n      .typewriter { width: calc(var(--chars) * 1ch); animation: caret 0.8s step-end infinite; }\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"typewriter\">Hello world</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
